author: @mdwasim959
text: Thats awesome one..whenever I see some coding of you I also try to do my way.. class Employee(): 	def __init__(self,n,a,s): 		self.n=n 		self.a=a 		self.s=s 	def __repr__(self): 		return '({},{},${})'.format(self.n,self.a,self.s) e1=Employee('carl',45,7000) e2=Employee('sarah',35,2000) e3=Employee('john',25,1000)  ee=[e1,e2,e3] l=[] for a in ee: 	l.append(a.s) print(sorted((l)))  Thanks for your awsome tutorial.. :)
